I"R<h2 id="about">About</h2>

<p>A <strong>horizontal rule</strong> is a component useful for separating content or adding a simmple accent to your content.</p>

<h2 id="example">Example</h2>

<p>Simply add the <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;hr&gt;</code> tag to your content to add the horizontal rule.</p>

<div class="bd-example">
<div class="bd-example">
	<p>This is a paragraph that I want to separate from the paragraph below.</p>
	<hr />
	<p>This is the other paragraph, which is separate from the one above.</p>
</div>
</div>
<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-html" data-lang="html"><span class="nt">&lt;div</span> <span class="na">class=</span><span class="s">"bd-example"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
	<span class="nt">&lt;p&gt;</span>This is a paragraph that I want to separate from the paragraph below.<span class="nt">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
	<span class="nt">&lt;hr&gt;</span>
	<span class="nt">&lt;p&gt;</span>This is the other paragraph, which is separate from the one above.<span class="nt">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;/div&gt;</span></code></pre></figure>
